}In the above program, the expressionxis an lvalue expression as it evaluates to variablex(which has an identifier).Since the introduction of constants into the language, lvalues come in two subtypes: amodifiable lvalueis an lvalue whose value can be modified. Anon-modifiable lvalueis an lvalue whose value can’t be modified (because the lvalue is const or constexpr).int main()
